               <physDesc>
                  <objectDesc>
                     <supportDesc>
                        <support>Parchment ; 17.5 x 15.0 cm</support>
                        <condition>
                           <ab type="conservation">Fine parchment, the length of which is intact, except perhaps for the loss of some of the lower margin.  A considerable part of the width is lost, the original size being approximately 20-22 cm.  What remains is in fair condition except for one large lacuna.</ab>
                        </condition>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout>
                           <ab type="lines">On recto and verso: 12 lines each in Arabic</ab>
                           <ab type="recto-verso">Source of description: On recto and verso: Qur'an</ab>
                        </layout>
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc>
                     <p>Small, but graceful Meccan script with comparatively long vertical strokes.  The ink must have been originally a light or medium brown because the recto is so faded that it looks blank and can be read only with great difficulty.  The verso shows a light and a dark shade of brown.  Vowel points are wanting, but diacritical strokes are freely used.  There is a note written in red in the margin of verso 2; it is in a different and later hand.</p>
                  </handDesc>
